This memorandum, issued by President Joseph R. Biden Jr. on December 7, 2023, delegates certain functions and authorities under the Uyghur Human Rights Policy Act of 2020 and Public Law 117-78 to the Secretary of State, the Secretary of the Treasury, and the Secretary of Homeland Security. The Secretary of State is delegated functions related to submitting reports and making determinations, while the Secretary of the Treasury is delegated functions related to making determinations and imposing sanctions. The Secretary of Homeland Security is delegated functions related to imposing sanctions. The memorandum also states that these delegations apply to future public laws with similar provisions. The Secretary of State is directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.